{"type":"message","id":"b4e80878","parentId":"99592746","timestamp":"2026-03-06T15:39:47.598Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Short answer: **no** — I don’t have a medical “kidney cancer detection” feature.\n\nI can help with:\n- explaining symptoms/risk factors in plain language,\n- helping you prepare questions for a doctor,\n- interpreting medical report text you share (non-diagnostic).\n\nBut I **can’t diagnose cancer** or replace imaging/lab review by a clinician.  \nIf this concern is personal and urgent (e.g., blood in urine, persistent flank pain, unexplained weight loss), it’s best to contact a doctor promptly.","textSignature":"msg_00afefed00d56ac90169aaf5406ba88191b1c09ec2de5e0528"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.3-codex","usage":{"input":7307,"output":118,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":7425,"cost":{"input":0.01278725,"output":0.001652,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01443925}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772811576095}}
